---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Nadhebe"
  description="Learn about our technical vision, Static architecture, and editorial process."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-24 py-64">
    <article class="prose-article">
      <h1>About Our Platform</h1>
      <p>
        Nadhebe is a highly optimized, fully static technical resource designed for developers, prompt engineers, and AI builders.
      </p>
      
      <h2>Our Technology Stack</h2>
      <p>
        This site is constructed on the modern <strong>Astro framework</strong> using <strong>Islands Architecture</strong>. We ship zero Client-side JavaScript by default, only hydrating interactive tools like search when needed. Every page maintains a perfect Lighthouse performance rating.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        We write in-depth tutorials, comparison reviews, and system prompt optimizations directly from developer testing. We reject thin, AI-generated spam content; every article answers specific search intents and undergoes thorough review.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
